The '''Galactic Justice Center''' was a massive government building on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. Located in [[Quadrant A-89]] of the [[Senate District/Legends|Senate District]], the main building of the complex was shaped like a giant cylinder plated with reflective [[Transparisteel/Legends|transparisteel]]. It contained several courthouses and other judicial and [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|law enforcement]] facilities.

==History==
The Justice Center was constructed sometime before the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]] that started in [[3653 BBY]]. It was destroyed during the [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|Battle of Coruscant]] and rebuilt under the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] after the end of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. During the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], the Justice Center housed the headquarters of the [[Galactic Alliance Guard]].<ref name="Bloodlines" />

This incarnation of the Galactic Justice Center was destroyed in [[44 ABY]], during the [[Liberation of Coruscant (Lost Tribe of Sith emergence)|Liberation of Coruscant]]. The [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] entity [[Abeloth]], who had been masquerading as [[Chief of State (Galactic Alliance)|Chief of State]] [[Rokari Kem]] and was leading the [[Lost Tribe of Sith]] forces in the [[New Jedi Temple|Jedi Temple]], caused widespread seismic and volcanic activity across the planet to distract the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], enabling her to escape with [[Ben Skywalker]] and [[Vestara Khai]]. The Justice Center was destroyed by a column of magma which burst from a volcano erupting underneath, sending what was left of the building crashing down into the [[Coruscant Underworld/Legends|undercity]].<ref name="Apocalypse" />

